cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Alma — A Proactive AI Emotional Companion for Mental Health"
message: "If you reference Alma in academic, applied, or evaluative work, please cite this repository."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "iDeepBrain Team"
    website: "https://github.com/iDeepBrain"
repository-code: "https://github.com/iDeepBrain/claude-hackathon-alma"
url: "https://alma-bot.com"
version: "2.0.0"
date-released: 2026-04-27
license: MIT
abstract: >
  Alma is a proactive AI emotional companion for mental health that takes the
  first step instead of waiting for the user to open the app. Built on Claude
  Opus 4.7 with Haiku 4.5 routing and Gemini Pro failover, Alma is deployed on
  Google Cloud Run with a four-layer semantic memory in Postgres + pgvector
  (HNSW), deterministic crisis detection with a dual-caller pattern, and three
  daily Redis-gated proactive check-ins. Bilingual Spanish and English,
  available on web (https://alma-bot.com) and Telegram. The repository
  documents the architecture, decision log, and post-hackathon evolution.
keywords:
  - mental health
  - companion AI
  - proactive AI
  - Claude
  - Anthropic
  - pgvector
  - HNSW
  - crisis detection
  - Cloud Run
  - multi-agent
  - emotional support
